🚨 The Problem: The "Chicken-and-Egg" Trap
Look closely at your configuration. You are telling Terraform two conflicting things:

In main.tf: "Hey Terraform, please create a brand new S3 bucket named abhishek-s3-demo-xyz."

In backend.tf: "Hey Terraform, before you do anything, connect to the S3 bucket named abhishek-s3-demo-xyz so I can store my state file there."

When you type terraform init, Terraform reads backend.tf first. It tries to connect to the S3 bucket to initialize the remote state. Because the bucket does not exist yet (since terraform apply hasn't been run), terraform init will fail with an error saying the S3 bucket cannot be found.

🛠️ The Correct 2-Step Workflow
To make this configuration work, you have to split your execution into two phases.

Phase 1: Create the Infrastructure Locally
First, you need to create the S3 bucket and DynamoDB table using a local state file.

Comment out or delete the entire backend.tf file (or the terraform { backend "s3" { ... } } block).

Run terraform init. (This initializes Terraform using your local hard drive to store the state file).

Run terraform apply.

This will successfully build your aws_instance.

It will create your aws_s3_bucket (abhishek-s3-demo-xyz).

It will create your aws_dynamodb_table (terraform-lock).

At this point, your S3 bucket and DynamoDB table finally exist in the real world on AWS.

Phase 2: Migrate your State to S3
Now that the bucket actually exists, you can tell Terraform to move your state file into it.

Uncomment your backend.tf file so it looks exactly like your code above.

Run terraform init again.

Terraform will detect that you just added a remote backend configuration. It will display a prompt in your terminal asking something like:

"Do you want to copy existing state to the new backend?"

Type yes.

Result: Terraform will automatically take your local state file, upload it securely into your newly created S3 bucket under the path abhi/terraform, and lock it using your new DynamoDB table. From that moment forward, your state lives permanently in S3!


